# Types and Constants Placement

## Interfaces and Types

All TypeScript interfaces, type aliases, and Zod schemas must live in a dedicated `.types.ts` file — never inline in service, controller, or route files.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — interface defined in service file
// scrape.service.ts
interface SearchResult { ... }
export function search(): SearchResult { ... }

// ✅ GOOD — interface in types file, imported where needed
// scrape.types.ts
export interface SearchResult { ... }

// scrape.service.ts
import type { SearchResult } from "./scrape.types.ts";
export function search(): SearchResult { ... }
```

- **Feature-specific types** → `src/features/<feature>/<feature>.types.ts`
- **Shared types** → `src/types/`

## Constants

All constants (`const` values used as configuration, defaults, or fixed data) must live in a dedicated `.constants.ts` file — never inline in service or controller files.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — constant defined in service file
// scrape.service.ts
const DEFAULT_PAGE_COUNT = 1;

// ✅ GOOD — constant in constants file
// scrape.constants.ts
export const DEFAULT_PAGE_COUNT = 1;

// scrape.service.ts
import { DEFAULT_PAGE_COUNT } from "./scrape.constants.ts";
```

- **Feature-specific constants** → `src/features/<feature>/<feature>.constants.ts`
- **Shared constants** → `src/configs/` or a shared `constants.ts`
